fields.description: A group of disorders affecting movement, muscle tone, and posture. In some cases, cognitive impairment may also be present.
A neural tube defect that can result in varying degrees of physical disability.
A collection of genetic disorders that cause progressive muscle weakness and degeneration.
A chronic disease affecting the central nervous system, often leading to physical impairments over time.
While primarily known for affecting cognitive functions, TBIs can also result in significant physical impairments.
A genetic condition caused by an extra copy of chromosome 21, often associated with mild to moderate intellectual disability along with potential physical health issues.
The most common inherited form of intellectual disability, resulting from a genetic mutation that affects brain development.
Although autism is primarily characterized by challenges with social interaction and communication, a subset of individuals on the spectrum may also have co-occurring intellectual disabilities.
A range of effects that can occur in individuals whose mothers consumed alcohol during pregnancy, potentially leading to intellectual and developmental disabilities.
